def plot_overdue_rate(subplot_index, df_list, labels, xlabel, title):
    overdue_rates = []
    for df in df_list:
        rate = df[''].sum() / (df[''].sum() + df[''].sum()) * 100
        overdue_rates.append(rate)
    plt.subplot(2, 3, subplot_index)
    plt.bar(labels, overdue_rates, color='skyblue')
    for i, val in enumerate(overdue_rates):
        plt.text(i, val + 0.3, f'{val:.2f}%', ha='center')
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(' (%)')
    plt.title(title)

# 
def group_by_category(df, col, values):
    return [df[df[col] == val] for val in values]

# 
def group_by_amount(df):
    bins = [0, 2000, 3500, 5500, float('inf')]
    labels = ['0-2000', '2000-3500', '3500-5500', '5500+']
    df[''] = pd.cut(df[''], bins=bins, labels=labels, right=False)
    return group_by_category(df, '', labels), labels

# 
def group_by_age(df):
    bins = [17, 25, 30, 35, 40, float('inf')]
    labels = ['17-25', '25-30', '30-35', '35-40', '40+']
    df[''] = pd.cut(df[''], bins=bins, labels=labels, right=False)
    return group_by_category(df, '', labels), labels

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))

def plot_interest_rate(subplot_index, df_list, labels, xlabel, title):
    avg_interest_rates = []
    for df in df_list:
        avg = df[''].mean()
        avg_interest_rates.append(avg)
    plt.subplot(2, 3, subplot_index)
    plt.bar(labels, avg_interest_rates, color='skyblue')
    for i, val in enumerate(avg_interest_rates):
        plt.text(i, val + 0.1, f'{val:.2f}%', ha='center')
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(' (%)')
    plt.title(title)

def calculate_reborrow_days(dates):
    if len(dates) >= 2:
        return (dates[1] - dates[0]).days

# --- 1. RFM---
rfm = cleaned_LC.groupby('ListingId').agg(
    Recency=('', lambda x: (pd.to_datetime('today') - x.max()).days),
    Frequency=('ListingId', 'count'),  # 1
    Monetary=('', 'sum')
)

# --- 2. ---
def safe_cut(series, bins=5, reverse=False):
    """"""
    labels = list(range(1, bins+1))
    if reverse: 
        labels = labels[::-1]
    # 
    if series.nunique() == 1:
        return pd.Series(labels[len(labels)//2], index=series.index)
    return pd.cut(series, bins=bins, labels=labels)

# 
rfm['R_Score'] = safe_cut(rfm['Recency'], bins=5, reverse=True)  # Recency
rfm['F_Score'] = safe_cut(rfm['Frequency'], bins=5)             # 13
rfm['M_Score'] = safe_cut(rfm['Monetary'], bins=5)

# --- 3.  ---
rfm[''] = (
    rfm['R_Score'].astype(str) + 
    rfm['M_Score'].astype(str)    # Frequency3R+M
)

# 
rfm[''] = rfm[''].map({
    '51': '','31': ''
}).fillna('')

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
rfm[''].value_counts().plot.pie(
    autopct='%1.1f%%', 
    startangle=90,
    wedgeprops={'width':0.4, 'edgecolor':'w'}
)
plt.title('')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.show()

#
def repayhabit(group,num,idx,xlabel,color):
    # 
    onetime = []
    for a in group:
        ot = a.loc[a[''] == 3][''].sum(
            ) + a.loc[a[''] == 3][''].sum()
        onetime.append(ot)
    # 
    partial = []
    for a in group:
        pa = a.loc[(a[''] == 1) & (a[''] < a[''])][''].sum(
            ) + a.loc[(a[''] == 1) & (a[''] < a[''])][''].sum()
        partial.append(pa)
    # 
    pastdue = []
    for a in group:
        pas = a.loc[(a[''] == 2) | (a[''] == 4)|(a[''] == 0)][''].sum() + \
            a.loc[(a[''] == 2) | (a[''] == 4)|(a[''] == 0)][''].sum()
        pastdue.append(pas)
    # 
    normal = []
    for a in group:
        nm = a.loc[(a[''] == 1) & (a[''] == a[''])][''].sum(
        ) + a.loc[(a[''] == 1) & (a[''] == a[''])][''].sum()
        normal.append(nm)
    
    tot = []
    for i in range(num):
        t = onetime[i]+partial[i]+pastdue[i]+normal[i]
        tot.append(t)

    print(tot)

    temp = []
    for i in range(num):
        tp = (100 * onetime[i] / tot[i], 100 * partial[i] / tot[i],
                100 * normal[i] / tot[i], 100 * pastdue[i] / tot[i])
        temp.append(tp)
        
    df = pd.DataFrame(temp)
    df.index = idx
    df.columns = ('', '', '', '')
    print(df)

    df.plot(kind='bar', colormap=color, stacked=True)
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
